        <div class="about-container">
          <h1>About Baliwag!</h1>
          <p>
            Baliwag, a progressive municipality in Bulacan. Known for its flourishing <br> industries, skilled manpower, and cultural heritage. 
            The town is home to <br> popular events like Baliwag Lechon, Baliwag Transit, and the longest Lenten <br> Procession in the country. 
            Baliwag is also the birthplace of Mariano Ponce <br> and Gliceria Rustia-Tantoco, two prominent Filipino business pioneers. <br>
            The municipality is committed to food security, dedicating 75% of its land for <br> agriculture, and follows the principle 
            of Serbisyong May Malasakit. <br> Visit Baliwag and experience its beauty and hospitality.
          </p>
        </div>
